# Project Structure

softwhere.uz is a Next.js 16 (App Router) multilingual marketing site, portfolio, AI-generated blog, cost estimator, and admin panel, written in TypeScript and organized into four enforced layers: `core` -> `shared` -> `modules` -> `app`.

## At a glance

| Layer | Path | May import from | Holds |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `core` | `src/core/**` | `core` only | Framework-agnostic infra: DB client, AI, HTTP client, auth, logger, env, i18n config, constants |
| `shared` | `src/shared/**` | `core`, `shared` | Cross-feature UI (Header, Footer, sections), fonts, shared types/utils/data |
| `modules` | `src/modules/*/**` | `core`, `shared`, own module | Feature slices: `admin`, `blog`, `contact`, `estimator` |
| `app` | `src/app/**` | anything | Next.js routes, pages, layouts, API route handlers |

The `@/*` path alias maps to `./src/*` (`tsconfig.json`). Layer rules are enforced by `eslint-plugin-boundaries` in `eslint.config.mjs` (see `development-guidelines.mdc`).

## `core/` infrastructure

Every file under `src/core` is importable from any layer. Key modules:

| File | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `src/core/db.ts` | Neon (serverless Postgres) via Drizzle's HTTP driver; exports a lazy `db` proxy |
| `src/core/http.ts` | Generic `apiClient` HTTP client + `ApiResponse<T>` / `AppError` types |
| `src/core/ai.ts` | AI generation over the OpenAI-compatible SDK (Kimi K2.6 primary, DeepSeek fallback) |
| `src/core/auth.ts` | `requireAdmin` route guard (Neon Auth session OR `Bearer API_SECRET`), locale validators |
| `src/core/neonAuth.ts` | Lazy Neon Auth (Better Auth) server instance via `getAuth()` |
| `src/core/logger.ts` | Structured `logger` singleton (the sanctioned `console` boundary) |
| `src/core/env.ts` | Startup env validation (`validateEnvironment`) |
| `src/core/constants.ts` | App constants (`BLOG_CONFIG`, `UI_CONFIG`, `CONTACT_INFO`, `ENV`, ...) |
| `src/core/i18n.ts` | next-intl `getRequestConfig` (locale resolution + message loading) |
| `src/core/notify.ts` | Telegram notification helper |

## Entry points

### Pages (`src/app/[locale]/`)
- Home: `src/app/[locale]/page.tsx` (composes `shared/components/sections/*`)
- Blog listing: `src/app/[locale]/blog/page.tsx`
- Blog post: `src/app/[locale]/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`
- Estimator: `src/app/[locale]/estimator/page.tsx`
- Admin posts: `src/app/[locale]/admin/posts/page.tsx` (plus `new/`, `edit/[postId]/`, `loading.tsx`)
- Admin leads: `src/app/[locale]/admin/leads/page.tsx`
- Layouts: `src/app/layout.tsx` (root), `src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx`, `src/app/[locale]/admin/layout.tsx`

### Non-page routes (`src/app/`)
- SEO: `src/app/robots.ts`, `src/app/sitemap.ts`, `src/app/[locale]/feed.xml/route.ts`, `src/app/api/og/route.tsx`

### API route handlers (`src/app/api/`)
- Blog: `blog/posts/route.ts`, `blog/posts/[slug]/route.ts`, `blog/posts/related/route.ts`, `blog/generate/route.ts`
- Admin: `admin/posts/route.ts`, `admin/posts/[id]/route.ts`, `admin/leads/route.ts`, `admin/revalidate/route.ts`
- Contact / estimator: `contact/route.ts`, `estimate/route.ts`, `estimate/lead/route.ts`, `currency/rates/route.ts`
- Auth (Neon Auth catch-all): `auth/[...path]/route.ts`
- Health: `health/route.ts`, `health/db/route.ts`

## Modules (`src/modules/`)

Each feature slice keeps its own model/components/api/utils. A module may import `core`, `shared`, and only its **own** module.

| Module | Notable contents |
| --- | --- |
| `blog` | `model/BlogPost.ts` (Drizzle schema), `model/posts.repository.ts` (DB access), `api/posts.ts` (client HTTP), `api/generator.ts` + `api/pipeline.ts` (server-only generation), `components/`, `data/`, `utils/`, `lib/seo.tsx` |
| `contact` | `model/Lead.ts` (Drizzle schema), `model/leads.repository.ts` |
| `estimator` | `api.ts` (client HTTP), `utils/estimator.ts` (formula), `data/catalog.ts`, `components/Wizard.tsx` + `Steps/`, `types.ts`, `constants.ts` |
| `admin` | UI kit `components/Admin*.tsx`, `utils/adminFetch.ts`, `utils/authClient.ts`, `utils/markdown.ts` |

## Database tables

Two Postgres tables, each defined as a Drizzle schema and reachable **only** through a repository (see `api-migration.mdc`):

| Table | Schema | Repository |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `blog_posts` | `src/modules/blog/model/BlogPost.ts` | `src/modules/blog/model/posts.repository.ts` |
| `leads` | `src/modules/contact/model/Lead.ts` | `src/modules/contact/model/leads.repository.ts` |

Both schemas are registered in `drizzle.config.ts` for `yarn db:push` / `db:generate` / `db:studio`.

## Internationalization

Three locales — `uz` (default), `ru`, `en` — via next-intl. Config: `src/core/i18n.ts`; middleware: `src/proxy.ts` (www-stripping, `/` -> `/uz`, locale routing); messages: `src/messages/{uz,ru,en}.json`. Blog posts translated across locales share a `generationGroupId`.

## Admin access

The admin UI lives under `src/app/[locale]/admin/**` and is gated by `requireAdmin` (`src/core/auth.ts`): a Neon Auth session with the `admin` role, or a `Bearer ${API_SECRET}` header for machine callers.

